00:56:29,200 --> 00:56:30,230
Did you eat?

821
00:56:31,400 --> 00:56:33,000
Are you eating your meals?

822
00:56:33,630 --> 00:56:35,000
(Gosh.)

823
00:56:35,800 --> 00:56:36,870
(Of course.)

824
00:56:37,140 --> 00:56:40,640
(Gosh. You're worried about my meals now.)

825
00:56:46,480 --> 00:56:47,650
What's wrong, Si-a?

826
00:56:50,480 --> 00:56:51,590
Dad.

827
00:56:53,720 --> 00:56:55,260
I miss you.

828
00:56:57,190 --> 00:56:58,730
(I miss you.)

829
00:57:04,200 --> 00:57:06,200
I miss you, Dad.

830
00:57:18,780 --> 00:57:19,850
I'm sorry.

831
00:57:21,920 --> 00:57:23,150
I'm sorry, Si-a.

832
00:57:26,320 --> 00:57:29,490
Dad. You'll come and see me, right?

833
00:57:59,290 --> 00:58:00,390
Si-a.

834
00:58:02,020 --> 00:58:03,160
I will make sure

835
00:58:08,430 --> 00:58:09,600
to be there.

836
00:58:56,810 --> 00:59:00,280
(Hong Dae-young)

837
00:59:06,390 --> 00:59:07,690
Why did you call me again?

838
00:59:09,590 --> 00:59:10,930
I have something to tell you.

839
00:59:11,330 --> 00:59:13,230
I have nothing to tell you.

840
00:59:13,890 --> 00:59:15,200
I'm near our house.

841
00:59:16,900 --> 00:59:18,900
I want to tell you this in person.

842
00:59:23,670 --> 00:59:24,670
Okay.

843
01:00:19,360 --> 01:00:20,530
Where are you?

844
01:00:55,460 --> 01:00:56,460
Da-jung.

845
01:00:58,430 --> 01:00:59,600
I'm Dae-young.

846
01:01:03,340 --> 01:01:04,710
I'm not Go Woo-young.

847
01:01:06,510 --> 01:01:07,580
I'm Hong Dae-young.

848
01:01:43,010 --> 01:01:44,550
- Over here.
- She's gorgeous.

849
01:01:44,550 --> 01:01:46,580
(3 years ago)
- In 1, 2. - Look here!

850
01:01:47,450 --> 01:01:48,480
- Look over here too.
- Great.

851
01:01:48,550 --> 01:01:50,580
Hey, can you look over here too?

852
01:01:51,650 --> 01:01:53,050
- You look so pretty.
- You look beautiful.

853
01:01:53,120 --> 01:01:55,690
Bride, please look over here. 1, 2.

854
01:01:55,960 --> 01:01:58,360
- All right. Great. How beautiful.
- So pretty.

855
01:02:00,330 --> 01:02:01,900
Hey, girl!

856
01:02:02,400 --> 01:02:03,860
My gosh. Hey, you!

857
01:02:03,930 --> 01:02:05,630
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

858
01:02:05,700 --> 01:02:08,370
- Your dress looks so beautiful.
- Look at her.

859
01:02:08,440 --> 01:02:10,040
All right. Let's take another one.

860
01:02:10,100 --> 01:02:11,940
- Okay. 1, 2.
- No.

861
01:02:12,810 --> 01:02:14,380
Your dress looks gorgeous.

862
01:02:31,690 --> 01:02:34,700
The bride looked really pretty.

863
01:02:37,160 --> 01:02:39,870
I know it's late,
but should we have a wedding?

864
01:02:41,700 --> 01:02:42,700
No.

865
01:02:43,270 --> 01:02:46,170
It'll cost a fortune to plan a wedding.

866
01:02:46,540 --> 01:02:50,240
Let's go on a trip with Si-a and Si-woo
with that money instead.

867
01:02:50,310 --> 01:02:52,150
I really want to make

868
01:02:52,210 --> 01:02:55,620
a lot of good memories for our children.

869
01:02:57,020 --> 01:02:58,020
That's all I want.

870
01:03:01,560 --> 01:03:03,120
- Here.
- What?

871
01:03:03,760 --> 01:03:04,830
I'm fine.

872
01:03:05,290 --> 01:03:06,660
I'm not fine with that.

873
01:03:07,600 --> 01:03:08,730
Cover yourself with that.

874
01:03:09,000 --> 01:03:10,000
I'll go buy an umbrella.

875
01:03:24,610 --> 01:03:25,850
What were you looking at?

876
01:03:26,650 --> 01:03:27,620
Nothing.

877
01:03:28,050 --> 01:03:31,550
I didn't know I would change like this
when I was young.

878
01:03:33,050 --> 01:03:34,050
"Change"?

879
01:03:34,760 --> 01:03:36,160
You haven't changed one bit.

880
01:03:40,360 --> 01:03:41,530
You must be cold.

881
01:03:42,060 --> 01:03:43,030
I'm fine.

882
01:03:43,600 --> 01:03:44,530
Well,

883
01:03:45,330 --> 01:03:47,130
can you accept this?

884
01:03:49,640 --> 01:03:50,870
What a surprise.

885
01:03:51,110 --> 01:03:52,110
Thank you.

886
01:03:58,950 --> 01:04:00,650
Why are you staring at me?

887
01:04:02,980 --> 01:04:04,120
Because you're pretty.

888
01:04:18,300 --> 01:04:19,300
I'm sorry.

889
01:04:20,670 --> 01:04:22,940
And thank you.

890
01:04:23,370 --> 01:04:24,870
To me, you are still

891
01:04:26,270 --> 01:04:28,380
the most beautiful woman in this world.

892
01:04:41,820 --> 01:04:42,860
Let's go now.

893
01:04:50,930 --> 01:04:52,130
(To be honest,)

894
01:04:52,630 --> 01:04:54,970
(my heart fluttered)

895
01:04:56,170 --> 01:04:57,370
for Woo-young.

896
01:04:57,910 --> 01:05:00,540
But the thing is

897
01:05:03,010 --> 01:05:04,950
I'm not sure if my heart fluttered

898
01:05:06,410 --> 01:05:08,720
because it was Woo-young

899
01:05:09,120 --> 01:05:10,680
or because he resembled Dae-young.

900
01:05:11,090 --> 01:05:12,350
Woo-young

901
01:05:13,720 --> 01:05:16,860
has his looks and his voice.

902
01:05:18,230 --> 01:05:20,460
He even behaves like Dae-young.

903
01:05:22,600 --> 01:05:24,060
When I see Woo-young,

904
01:05:26,970 --> 01:05:28,840
I keep thinking about Hong Dae-young

905
01:05:30,370 --> 01:05:32,310
whom my heart fluttered for before.

906
01:05:35,080 --> 01:05:37,140
But why is he acting

907
01:05:37,240 --> 01:05:40,810
just like Dae-young with the same looks?

908
01:05:41,820 --> 01:05:43,080
Da-jung.

909
01:05:43,780 --> 01:05:45,620
- The truth is...
- Right.

910
01:05:45,950 --> 01:05:47,350
It's my fault.

911
01:05:47,760 --> 01:05:51,260
I should draw a line starting right now.

912
01:05:51,690 --> 01:05:54,190
I should tell him that I'm a parent
and he's a student.

913
01:05:54,360 --> 01:05:55,430
I'll get going now.

914
01:06:00,130 --> 01:06:01,300
Da-jung!

915
01:06:02,940 --> 01:06:05,510
Gosh. I don't know anymore.

916
01:06:06,770 --> 01:06:07,880
But

917
01:06:08,840 --> 01:06:11,210
she told me her heart
didn't flutter for her husband.
